2.1 Auth-source
===============

For locked (i.e.  encrypted) disks, passwords are obtained from
auth-source or directly from user prompt.  If
‘udisksctl-use-auth-source-passwords’ customisation variable is nil,
then auth-source is not used.

   It is recommended to use KWallet with auth-source by using
auth-source-kwallet.  See auth-source-kwallet home page
(https://github.com/vaartis/auth-source-kwallet) for more information.
It is also available as a MELPA package.  It requires the following
use-package snippet:

     (use-package auth-source-kwallet
       :config
       (auth-source-kwallet-enable))

   Or use the following Elisp to load the package:

     (require 'auth-source-kwallet)
     (auth-source-kwallet-enable)


