3.1.3 A mount type section-data
-------------------------------

A parsed mount section-data is as follows:

     (("type" "org.freedesktop.UDisks2.Filesystem")
     ("MountPoints" ("/" "/gnu/store"))
     ("Size" "104855502848"))

   This is provided by the mount points found on the original text.
This is not useful for representing all elements as the device is not
present.  When user select this option, the program cannot determine the
device is referring these mountpoints.  To complete all the alist data,
the previous section-data is used (which it is expected to be a
device-type if the original text is provided), and in this case, all
information needed is stored for future usage.

